---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Tenets | Grithos"
  description="The fifteen tenets of Grithos — three per pillar, practiced daily. Truth, strength, control, legacy, and verity. The rules a Grithosian lives by, every single day."
  ogTitle="The Fifteen Tenets — Grithos"
  ogDescription="Fifteen tenets across five pillars. Truth, strength, control, legacy, and verity. The daily practice of living with grit and ethos."
  ogUrl="https://grithos.com/tenets"
  canonical="https://grithos.com/tenets"
  activePage="tenets"
>

<style is:inline>
  /* ═══ PAGE HERO ═══ */
  .page-hero {
    padding: 80px 0 40px;
    text-align: center;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .page-hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 40%; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 800px; height: 800px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(196,168,130,.05) 0%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }
  .page-hero .wrap { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .page-hero-overline {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: .18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .page-hero-title {
    font-family: var(--heading);
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 52px);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -.02em;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .page-hero-sub {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(16px, 2vw, 20px);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ═══ PREAMBLE ═══ */
  .preamble {
    padding: 28px 0;
  }
  .preamble-text {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.9;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  /* ═══ SECTION DIVIDER ═══ */
  .section-divider {
    width: 100%;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ═══ TENETS GROUP ═══ */
  .tenets-group {
    padding: 28px 0;
  }
  .tenets-group-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .tenets-group-pillar {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: .18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .tenets-group-name {
    font-family: var(--heading);
    font-size: clamp(24px, 3vw, 36px);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    letter-spacing: -.01em;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .tenets-group-tagline {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 16px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  /* ═══ TENET CARD ═══ */
  .tenet {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 0 20px;
    scroll-margin-top: 100px;
  }
  .tenet + .tenet {
    padding-top: 20px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .tenet-number {
    font-family: var(--heading);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: .22em;
    color: var(--gold);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .tenet-title {
    font-family: var(--heading);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.5vw, 26px);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    letter-spacing: -.01em;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  /* ═══ WISDOM SECTIONS ═══ */
  .tenet-section-label {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: .18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  .tenet-body {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .tenet-body p + p {
    margin-top: 16px;
  }

  .tenet-ancient {
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .tenet-ai-age {
    padding-top: 20px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(196,168,130,.08);
  }
  .tenet-ai-age .tenet-body {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* ═══ CLOSING ═══ */
  .closing {
    padding: 28px 0 32px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .closing-text {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.8vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--white);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto 24px;
  }
  .closing-sub {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 18px);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ═══ BACK LINK ═══ */
  .back-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color .2s;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--gold); }
  .back-link svg { width: 16px; height: 16px; }

  /* ═══ RESPONSIVE ═══ */
  @media(max-width:768px) {
    .tenets-group { padding: 28px 0; }
    .tenet { padding: 0 0 16px; }
    .tenet + .tenet { padding-top: 16px; }
  }
</style>

<!-- ═══ HERO ═══ -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="reveal d1">
      <img src="/assets/images/grithos-logo.png" alt="Grithos" style="width: 120px; height: auto; margin-bottom: 16px; opacity: 0.85;">
      <p class="page-hero-overline">The Daily Practice</p>
      <h1 class="page-hero-title">The Fifteen Tenets</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-sub">A Grithosian does not just believe. A Grithosian practices.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<!-- ═══ PREAMBLE ═══ -->
<section class="preamble">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="reveal d1">
      <p class="preamble-text">The Five Pillars define what a Grithosian stands for. The Fifteen Tenets define how a Grithosian lives. These are not aspirations. They are practices — daily, deliberate, and non-negotiable. Read them. Internalize them. Then go live them.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<!-- ═══ TENETS OF VIRTUE ═══ -->
<section class="tenets-group" id="virtue-tenets">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="tenets-group-header reveal d1">
      <p class="tenets-group-pillar">From Pillar I — Virtue</p>
      <h2 class="tenets-group-name">Do Right Regardless</h2>
      <p class="tenets-group-tagline">Three tenets for the honest life.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET I -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d2" id="tenet-i">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet I</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Tell the Truth. Even When It Costs You.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>A Grithosian does not bend the truth to protect comfort — theirs or anyone else's. You say what is real. You report what happened. You admit what you did. Not because it is easy. Because it is right.</p>
        <p>If the truth costs you a friendship, a deal, a promotion — you pay that price and you sleep well. A life built on lies is a life built on sand. A Grithosian builds on stone.</p>
        <p>The cost of lying has never been lower. A manufactured narrative takes seconds. Everyone can polish reality into something more comfortable. That is exactly why telling the truth has never mattered more. When the world is drowning in noise, your honest word becomes the rarest signal on earth. Be that signal.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET II -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d3" id="tenet-ii">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet II</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Keep Your Word Like Your Life Depends on It.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>When a Grithosian says they will do something, it is done. No qualifiers. No escape clauses. No "I'll try." You said it. Now you do it.</p>
        <p>This means you speak carefully. You do not make promises you cannot keep. You do not commit to things you have no intention of finishing. Your word is the most valuable thing you own. Treat it that way.</p>
        <p>The modern world makes breaking commitments frictionless — an auto-reply, a quiet reschedule, a convenient excuse. That is not progress. That is erosion. Your commitments are not data points to be optimized. They are the architecture of your character. A tool can manage your calendar. Only you can honor what you said you would do.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET III -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d4" id="tenet-iii">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet III</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Own Your Wins. But Do Right in the Dark.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>When you do something great — say so. A Grithosian does not shrink from recognition. You built it. You earned it. Tell the world. Hiding your achievements is not humility. It is a betrayal of your apex nature.</p>
        <p>But here is the line that separates you: when no one is watching, when there is no audience, no reward, no applause — you still do right. Return the extra change. Tell the truth on the form. Do the work you said you did. The real measure of a Grithosian is not what you do under the spotlight. It is what you do in the dark.</p>
        <p>The age of inflated credentials is here. Polished portfolios you did not earn. Thought leadership you did not write. Everyone looks brilliant on screen. Fewer and fewer actually are. A Grithosian lets their actual work do the talking. When you use a tool — you say so. Integrity is not performing honesty for an audience. It is being honest when no system is tracking you at all.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<!-- ═══ TENETS OF APEX ═══ -->
<section class="tenets-group" id="apex-tenets">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="tenets-group-header reveal d1">
      <p class="tenets-group-pillar">From Pillar II — Apex</p>
      <h2 class="tenets-group-name">Own Your Nature</h2>
      <p class="tenets-group-tagline">Three tenets for the apex life.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET IV -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d2" id="tenet-iv">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet IV</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Never Shrink. Never Apologize for Strength.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>You are the most capable species on this planet. Act like it. Do not dim your light to make someone else comfortable. Do not play small because the world tells you ambition is arrogance.</p>
        <p>A Grithosian owns their capability completely. You are strong. You are sharp. You are built to lead. That is not ego — it is fact. Use it. Every day you play small is a day wasted.</p>
        <p>The machines are faster. They process more, produce more, and never need sleep. And now the world whispers that maybe you are not needed anymore. A Grithosian does not step aside. You are not a slower version of a computer. You are the thing that gives the output meaning. Judgment, courage, conviction, sacrifice — no machine replicates these. Apologizing for your strength because a tool is faster is like apologizing for your heartbeat because a clock keeps better time. You are apex. The tools serve you. Not the other way around.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET V -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d3" id="tenet-v">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet V</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Protect Those Beneath You.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>Apex is not a trophy. It is a weight. The strongest creature in the room has the greatest responsibility — not to dominate, but to protect. A Grithosian lifts the people around them.</p>
        <p>You mentor. You shield. You stand between the vulnerable and the harm that's coming for them. Not because they are weak — because you are strong enough to carry it. Power without protection is tyranny.</p>
        <p>Disruption does not displace everyone equally. It comes first for the people with the least leverage — the ones without networks, without capital, without the luxury of pivoting. A Grithosian does not hoard the advantage. You teach what you know. You pull people up — not out of charity, but because that is what apex demands. The strongest in the room does not watch the weakest get swept away and call it progress. You extend your hand. You share the knowledge. Your responsibility to the people counting on you never sleeps.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET VI -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d4" id="tenet-vi">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet VI</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Reject the Victim. Become the Author.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>Bad things happen. To everyone. A Grithosian does not deny hardship. They refuse to be defined by it. The moment you decide that what happened to you is bigger than what you do next — you have surrendered your apex nature.</p>
        <p>You are not what happened to you. You are what you choose to do now. Today. This hour. Feel the pain. Honor it. Then move. Write the next chapter yourself. You are the author, not the character.</p>
        <p>It has never been easier to blame forces beyond your control. The market shifted. The industry changed. Entire doors closed that you spent years walking through. That is the reality. But a Grithosian does not stand at closed doors reciting grievances. You learn the new tool. You build the new skill. You write the next chapter with whatever pen the age hands you. Author — not victim. Always.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<!-- ═══ TENETS OF CONTROL ═══ -->
<section class="tenets-group" id="control-tenets">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="tenets-group-header reveal d1">
      <p class="tenets-group-pillar">From Pillar III — Control</p>
      <h2 class="tenets-group-name">Live Within Bounds</h2>
      <p class="tenets-group-tagline">Three tenets for the disciplined life.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET VII -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d2" id="tenet-vii">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet VII</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Own Only What Is Yours.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>Your thoughts. Your decisions. Your effort. Your character. These four things are yours — completely and without exception. You own them. You fight for them. And you fight for the outcome too.</p>
        <p>But when the bounds decide otherwise — and sometimes they will — you do not shatter. You redirect. Other people's opinions, the economy, the weather, the diagnosis — these belong to the bounds, not to you. A Grithosian draws this line with absolute clarity every single day.</p>
        <p>You can delegate your tasks, your inbox, your analysis. Tools will handle all of it faster and cheaper. But no tool can carry your thoughts, your decisions, your effort, or your character. A Grithosian does not confuse delegation with abdication. The tool writes the report — you own the conclusion. The tool suggests the strategy — you own the decision. Automate everything you can. But never automate your accountability. That is yours. It will always be yours.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET VIII -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d3" id="tenet-viii">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet VIII</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Redirect Immediately.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>When the bounds close a door, a Grithosian does not stand there knocking. You do not rage at the wall. You do not collapse in the hallway. You turn. Immediately. Deliberately.</p>
        <p>Every ounce of energy that would have been spent fighting what you cannot change gets redirected — instantly — toward what you can. This is not cold. This is not heartless. This is the most efficient use of the only life you have. Do not waste it arguing with reality.</p>
        <p>The world is engineered to consume your attention. Every feed, every notification exists to keep you reacting instead of redirecting. A Grithosian guards their attention like it is oxygen — because it is. When a door closes, you do not scroll through the grief. You do not let distraction metabolize your frustration into wasted hours. You close the screen. You redirect. The most radical act of discipline is not productivity. It is choosing where your mind goes next — and refusing to let anything else make that choice for you.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET IX -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d4" id="tenet-ix">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet IX</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Trust the Bounds.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>God authored the bounds. They are rational. They are consistent. They are not punishment — they are structure. Gravity does not hate you for falling. It simply is.</p>
        <p>A Grithosian does not fight the bounds any more than a sailor fights the wind. You learn them. You respect them. You work within them. And when the bounds deliver something you did not choose — illness, loss, failure — you trust that the structure is still intact. The bounds are not your enemy. They are the floor you stand on.</p>
        <p>The great anxiety of any age is not what change will do to the world. It is what it does to your sense of purpose. When the ground shifts beneath you — when tools and systems transform faster than you can track — a Grithosian does not spiral. You trust the bounds. Your mortality, your relationships, your capacity to suffer and to love — none of that changed because the world moved faster. The real question is not what disruption will do to you. It is what you are doing with the time you have. The bounds still hold. Stand on them.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<!-- ═══ TENETS OF DEATH ═══ -->
<section class="tenets-group" id="death-tenets">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="tenets-group-header reveal d1">
      <p class="tenets-group-pillar">From Pillar IV — Death</p>
      <h2 class="tenets-group-name">Return to the Whole</h2>
      <p class="tenets-group-tagline">Three tenets for the finite life.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET X -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d2" id="tenet-x">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet X</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Live Like You Will Die. Because You Will.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>You are not promised tomorrow. A Grithosian does not push the important conversation to next week. Does not save the meaningful work for "someday." Does not assume there is more time.</p>
        <p>Death is not a threat. It is a deadline. And it is the most honest motivator you will ever have. Let it sharpen every decision. Let it burn away the trivial. You are alive right now. Act like it means something. Because it does.</p>
        <p>The optimists will always promise more time — a new breakthrough, a longer life, another decade on the horizon. The implicit message: you can afford to wait. A Grithosian does not bet their urgency on a promise. Nothing extends your meaning. The important conversation is still today. The meaningful work is still now. No amount of progress changes the fundamental equation: you are finite, and the clock does not care about your roadmap. Live like you will die. Because nothing has solved that one yet.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET XI -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d3" id="tenet-xi">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet XI</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Grieve Fully. Then Move.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>A Grithosian does not suppress grief. You feel it — every raw, gutting ounce of it. You feel it because you are apex. Because only a creature capable of deep love can experience deep loss. That pain is proof of what you built.</p>
        <p>But grief is not a residence. It is a passage. Feel it completely. Honor what was lost. Then stand up. Wipe your face. And move. Not because the pain is gone — because there is still life left to live and you will not waste it sitting in the dark.</p>
        <p>The world has never been better at helping you avoid your own pain. There is a distraction for every sorrow, a feed perfectly tuned to numb whatever you are feeling. A Grithosian does not anesthetize grief with a screen. You sit in it. You feel the weight. And when you are ready — not when the world decides you should be — you stand up. Endurance is not automated. Resilience is not a feature. These are human. The machine can optimize everything except the part that actually matters: getting back up.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET XII -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d4" id="tenet-xii">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet XII</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Build a Legacy That Stands in This Life.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-body">
        <p>A Grithosian builds something that matters right here, right now. You live for the impact you leave in the living. The person you mentored. The truth you told when it cost you everything. The moment you stood between the vulnerable and the harm.</p>
        <p>The universe is permanently and irrevocably different because you existed in it. That is your legacy — and it matters regardless of what comes next. You were here. You did right. You lived fully. Whatever awaits beyond, you will meet it with a life well-lived behind you.</p>
        <p>Output is no longer scarce. Anyone can flood the world with content before lunch. But legacy is not what you produced. It is what you changed. The life you altered by showing up when it was hard. The truth you defended when the crowd moved on. The person who is different because you existed — not your profile, not your portfolio, but you. The world does not need another creator. It needs someone who meant it. Be that someone.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<!-- ═══ TENETS OF VERITY ═══ -->
<section class="tenets-group" id="verity-tenets">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="tenets-group-header reveal d1">
      <p class="tenets-group-pillar">From Pillar V — Verity</p>
      <h2 class="tenets-group-name">Walk Forward. Eyes Open.</h2>
      <p class="tenets-group-tagline">Three tenets for the engineered age.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET XIII -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d2" id="tenet-xiii">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet XIII</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">The World Engineers Your Comfort. Master It Anyway.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-ancient">
        <div class="tenet-section-label">Ancient Wisdom</div>
        <div class="tenet-body">
          <p>The comfort trap is not new. Bread and circuses kept Rome docile. Opium kept empires asleep. Every age has its anesthetic — a system designed to make you stop asking questions and start accepting what you’re given.</p>
          <p>A Grithosian sees comfort for what it is: a tool of control. Not all comfort is bad. But comfort you didn’t choose, comfort engineered to keep you passive — that is a cage with a pillow inside it. The practice is awareness. Know what you’re consuming. Know who designed it. Know why.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tenet-ai-age">
        <div class="tenet-section-label">The AI Age</div>
        <div class="tenet-body">
          <p>The feed is not random. Your recommendations are not helpful suggestions. They are precision-engineered behavioral nudges, built by the most sophisticated pattern-matching systems ever created, tuned to keep you engaged, consuming, and predictable.</p>
          <p>A Grithosian does not unplug from the modern world — that is retreat, not mastery. You learn how the system works. You understand the algorithm. You use the tools on your terms, not theirs. Mastery is not avoidance. It is informed, deliberate engagement with a world that was engineered before you arrived.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET XIV -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d3" id="tenet-xiv">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet XIV</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Build With. Never Build Under.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-ancient">
        <div class="tenet-section-label">Ancient Wisdom</div>
        <div class="tenet-body">
          <p>Every great civilization rose when humans built tools that extended their reach — the lever, the wheel, the printing press. Every dark chapter began when people stopped being the ones holding the tools and became the resources the tools consumed.</p>
          <p>A Grithosian builds with their instruments, never under them. The tool serves you. The moment you serve the tool, you have surrendered your apex nature.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tenet-ai-age">
        <div class="tenet-section-label">The AI Age</div>
        <div class="tenet-body">
          <p>AI is the most powerful tool ever created. It writes, designs, codes, analyzes, and creates at a scale no human can match. The question is not whether you will use it. The question is whether you will use it — or it will use you.</p>
          <p>A Grithosian builds with AI as a partner, not a master. You direct the output. You own the decisions. You bring the judgment, the values, the conviction. The machine brings the speed. Build with. Never build under. That is the line between partnership and servitude.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TENET XV -->
    <div class="tenet reveal d4" id="tenet-xv">
      <div class="tenet-number">Tenet XV</div>
      <h3 class="tenet-title">Walk Forward. Eyes Open.</h3>

      <div class="tenet-ancient">
        <div class="tenet-section-label">Ancient Wisdom</div>
        <div class="tenet-body">
          <p>The future has always been uncertain. Every generation believed their age was the most dangerous, the most transformative, the most consequential. They were always right — for their time.</p>
